In this article, President Donald Trump proclaims November 2019 as National Family Caregivers Month. He recognizes and honors the selfless Americans who dedicate themselves to providing care and support to their ailing and aging loved ones. Caregivers assist their family members in various aspects of their lives, such as domestic, financial, and medical affairs, allowing them to live with dignity. The president emphasizes the importance of providing resources and respect to caregivers, which requires a commitment from community stakeholders and government at various levels. The article also mentions the establishment of the Family Caregiving Advisory Council and the Advisory Council to Support Grandparents Raising Grandchildren, which aim to strengthen the nation's support for family caregivers. The president encourages all Americans to reach out and thank those who provide care for their family members, friends, and neighbors in need.